<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="833" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Bowen</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-10"><hi rend="italic">January 10,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that Mr. Bowen’s arrival at Washington as Venezuela’s
                            plenipotentiary must be awaited before any preliminaries can be
                            adjusted, including the raising of the blockade, which may depend upon
                            sufficiency of guaranty.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>